## Commit humanizer — TOP PRIORITY (MUST)

**Priority:** highest among commit / git rules. Overrides convenience.
**Fail closed:** if message looks AI-generated or templated → **do not commit**.

### Gate: `isCommitedPassedHumanizer`

Before **any** `git commit` / amend:

1. Run mental check (agent) + repo checker:
   `node .githooks/check-commit-humanizer.mjs --stdin`
2. If it would fail → **STOP**. Rewrite message. Never `--no-verify`.
3. Git hook `.githooks/commit-msg` + Cursor hook `.cursor/hooks/block-ai-commit-msg.mjs` **block** bad messages.

### Hard BLOCK (must fail)

| Pattern | Example |
|---|---|
| AI trailers | `Co-Authored-By: Cursor …`, Claude, Copilot, ChatGPT, … |
| AI phrases | "Generated with", "Made with Cursor", 🤖, "as an AI" |
| Templated title | "Add X and fix Y" |
| Verb-first changelog | "Fix X", "Add Y", "Update Z", `feat:` … |
| Bullet-list body | multi `-` bullets explaining the change |

### Required shape (PASS)

- **Title only** by default (no essay body unless user asked).
- **Adjective Noun** short title — e.g. `Proper Icon`, `Sharper Sizing`, `Cleaner PI Schedule`.
- **No** AI co-author trailers unless user explicitly asks for that commit.
- Caveman line only if user opts in.

### Agent duties

1. Draft human title **first**; validate with checker **before** `git commit`.
2. If Cursor re-injects `Co-Authored-By` after commit → amend/strip (unpushed) or ask user.
3. Never suggest skipping the hook.
4. Install hooks once per clone: `bash scripts/install-git-hooks.sh`

### Amend

Unpushed HEAD you created + humanizer fail → amend to fix. Pushed → ask (force-push).
